Answer: B. Mg(NO_{3})_{2} + K_{2}CO_{3} -> MgCO_{3} + 2KNO_{3}

Reasoning: 
- Choice B balances the equation with 1 Mg, 2 N, 6 O from Mg(NO_{3})_{2} on the left, and 1 Mg, 2 N, 6 O on the right in MgCO_{3} + 2KNO_{3}. It also balances K and C with 2 K and 1 C on both sides. Other choices do not balance all elements equally.
